{
  "circuit": {
    "description": "TransGate canonical pass-through: vs=1V drives tg:out1; p1=1V (NFET drv ON, V(p1)-V(out2)>Vth), p2=0V (PFET drv ON, V(p2)-V(out2)<-Vth means we need a different bias; with Vth=0.5V default 2.5V we need both paths conducting); load Rload=1k from tg:out2 to ground. Both gates conducting -> series Ron path delivers near-vs to out2.",
